title: Air Fryer Oven Buffalo Chicken Jerky Sticks

Ingredients.2: 0.25 cup cayenne pepper sauce (such as Frank's® RedHot®)

Ingredients.9: 2 tablespoons cayenne pepper sauce (such as Frank's® RedHot®)

Directions.1: Combine ground chicken, 1/4 cup cayenne pepper sauce, sea salt, pepper, celery seed, garlic powder, onion powder, and pink curing salt in a large bowl; mix until evenly combined. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours, or overnight.

Directions.2: Use a jerky gun to form sticks of the meat mixture on air fryer oven racks.

Directions.3: Preheat the air fryer to 160 degrees F (70 degrees C).

Directions.4: Place racks into the air fryer and set timer for 2 hours. Flip the sticks over using a fork. Brush remaining 2 tablespoons cayenne pepper sauce over the tops. Air fry for 30 minutes more.

Directions.5: Let cool completely and transfer to an airtight container.
